<font color="yellow">I'll never let go of your hand from now on.</font>

201
00:14:56,459 --> 00:14:57,459
<font color="yellow">All right.</font>

202
00:14:58,101 --> 00:15:01,944
<font color="yellow">I cried so much after losing you.</font>

203
00:15:04,249 --> 00:15:09,217
<font color="yellow">I was so cold, hungry, and scared.</font>

204
00:15:11,264 --> 00:15:15,882
<font color="yellow">But father, the truth is...</font>

205
00:15:17,022 --> 00:15:18,428
<font color="yellow">I was so hungry...</font>

206
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:23,678
<font color="yellow">that I stole something just once.</font>

207
00:15:24,069 --> 00:15:25,069
<font color="yellow">What?</font>

208
00:15:26,179 --> 00:15:27,670
<font color="yellow">You stole something?</font>

209
00:15:28,014 --> 00:15:29,100
<font color="yellow">Yes.</font>

210
00:15:29,968 --> 00:15:31,968
<font color="yellow">I stole one dumpling and ate it.</font>

211
00:15:32,608 --> 00:15:34,608
<font color="yellow">One dumpling?</font>

212
00:15:35,686 --> 00:15:39,246
<font color="yellow">Oh my goodness. How hungry must
you have been to do something like that.</font>

213
00:15:40,569 --> 00:15:47,158
<font color="yellow">But Dae-hoon, the owner
would have understood you.</font>

214
00:15:47,663 --> 00:15:50,409
<font color="yellow">So don't blame yourself.</font>

215
00:15:50,968 --> 00:15:55,866
<font color="yellow">No, father. I really want to
pay that dumpling store back.</font>

216
00:15:56,483 --> 00:15:57,819
<font color="yellow">Sure, let's do that.</font>

217
00:15:58,514 --> 00:16:01,893
<font color="yellow">Let's go back there tomorrow and
pay them back for the dumpling.</font>

218
00:16:03,218 --> 00:16:04,218
<font color="yellow">Yes, father.</font>

219
00:16:05,210 --> 00:16:09,116
<font color="yellow">But that dumpling was so delicious.</font>

220
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:13,881
<font color="yellow">It tasted just like the
ones mother used to make.</font>

221
00:16:14,857 --> 00:16:15,857
<font color="yellow">Really?</font>

222
00:16:16,771 --> 00:16:18,329
<font color="yellow">While I ate that dumpling...</font>

223
00:16:20,779 --> 00:16:22,246
<font color="yellow">I thought of mother...</font>

224
00:16:24,591 --> 00:16:26,520
<font color="yellow">and cried so much.</font>

225
00:16:28,685 --> 00:16:29,685
<font color="yellow">You did?</font>

226
00:16:32,029 --> 00:16:37,013
<font color="yellow">I want to eat those dumplings, too.</font>

227
00:16:38,865 --> 00:16:42,314
<font color="yellow">Dae-hoon, let's go to that
dumpling store tomorrow,</font>

228
00:16:42,339 --> 00:16:45,381
<font color="yellow">pay them back for the dumpling you stole,</font>

229
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,661
<font color="yellow">and buy more dumplings to eat.</font>

230
00:16:48,615 --> 00:16:50,344
<font color="yellow">- Yes, father.
- Good.</font>

231
00:17:02,357 --> 00:17:03,357
<font color="yellow">Mom.</font>

232
00:17:04,779 --> 00:17:06,167
<font color="yellow">Are you thinking about father?</font>

233
00:17:08,529 --> 00:17:11,296
<font color="yellow">It must be because we saw those
people staying underground.</font>

234
00:17:12,786 --> 00:17:16,165
<font color="yellow">I keep thinking of so
many different possibilities.</font>

235
00:17:17,169 --> 00:17:20,419
<font color="yellow">Where is your father and what is he doing?</font>

236
00:17:21,474 --> 00:17:23,653
<font color="yellow">If he really is mentally unstable,</font>

237
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:29,692
<font color="yellow">did he get beaten up while trying
to steal food from somewhere else?</font>

238
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:34,802
<font color="yellow">Mom, why are you saying such nonsense?</font>

239
00:17:35,786 --> 00:17:37,832
<font color="yellow">You know father is a strong person.</font>

240
00:17:38,826 --> 00:17:42,075
<font color="yellow">If he's alive, he'll be safe.</font>

241
00:17:42,615 --> 00:17:43,798
<font color="yellow">I'm going to believe that.</font>

242
00:17:45,451 --> 00:17:46,451
<font color="yellow">Yes.</font>

243
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:48,147
<font color="yellow">That's true, right?</font>

244
00:17:49,787 --> 00:17:52,539
<font color="yellow">Mom, how about we give out
dumplings to those homeless people</font>

245
00:17:52,564 --> 00:17:55,465
<font color="yellow">living in that underground
tunnel every single day?</font>

246
00:17:55,779 --> 00:17:59,880
<font color="yellow">We won't be able to give much,
but wouldn't father come there</font>

247
00:17:59,905 --> 00:18:03,740
<font color="yellow">one day when he hears out
we're giving out free dumplings?</font>

248
00:18:05,427 --> 00:18:07,593
<font color="yellow">Yes, that's a good idea.</font>

249
00:18:08,568 --> 00:18:12,768
<font color="yellow">We can help those in need by
giving them the dumplings we made.</font>

250
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:17,209
<font color="yellow">It would be great if we could
find your father while doing that.</font>

251
00:18:17,234 --> 00:18:19,107
<font color="yellow">- Right?
- Yes, it's a good idea.</font>

252
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:22,949
<font color="yellow">We will need to work harder
and make more money if</font>

253
00:18:22,974 --> 00:18:25,342
<font color="yellow">we want to give many
dumplings to the homeless.</font>

254
00:18:25,873 --> 00:18:27,578
<font color="yellow">Yes, we will.</font>

255
00:18:27,974 --> 00:18:30,900
<font color="yellow">You're a much better person than I am.</font>

256
00:18:43,763 --> 00:18:47,616
<font color="yellow">Shin-ae said it was your birthday,
so she wanted me to secretly come</font>

257
00:18:47,641 --> 00:18:51,215
<font color="yellow">out to plan a surprise party for you.
That's why I had gone out.</font>

258
00:18:51,420 --> 00:18:52,802
<font color="yellow">When did I say that?</font>

259
00:18:53,709 --> 00:18:56,528
<font color="yellow">Dad, what's wrong with you?
Why are you making things up?</font>

260
00:18:56,716 --> 00:18:58,798
<font color="yellow">You told me to come out! You told me to meet</font>

261
00:18:58,823 --> 00:19:00,951
<font color="yellow">you in the alley next to the stationary store!</font>

262
00:19:01,427 --> 00:19:02,997
<font color="yellow">So why are you lying?</font>

263
00:19:05,513 --> 00:19:07,530
<font color="yellow">Did Shin-ae really...?</font>

264
00:19:10,685 --> 00:19:11,935
<font color="yellow">No.</font>

265
00:19:14,841 --> 00:19:18,614
<font color="yellow">Why would she make up such a lie?</font>

266
00:19:19,295 --> 00:19:20,390
<font color="yellow">Of course she wouldn't.</font>

267
00:19:22,779 --> 00:19:24,028
<font color="yellow">My goodness.</font>

268
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,161
<font color="yellow">Goodness.</font>

269
00:19:47,974 --> 00:19:54,935
<font color="yellow">You had witnessed your son and
wife being shot in front of your eyes.</font>

270
00:19:58,317 --> 00:20:00,575
<font color="yellow">Of course you wouldn't be sane.</font>

271
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,143
<font color="yellow">Still, it's okay.</font>

272
00:20:04,607 --> 00:20:05,607
<font color="yellow">It's okay.</font>

273
00:20:09,193 --> 00:20:12,583
<font color="yellow">You just have to stay by my side.</font>

274
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:31,198
<font color="yellow">Grandfather, are you going somewhere with dad?</font>

275
00:20:33,334 --> 00:20:38,339
<font color="yellow">I feel nervous about leaving
Dae-hoon at home by himself.</font>

276
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:40,615
<font color="yellow">I'm going to take him
around with me for a while.</font>

277
00:20:41,176 --> 00:20:47,254
<font color="yellow">Last time I wasn't home, so that
incident occurred, but don't worry now.</font>

278
00:20:47,795 --> 00:20:51,573
<font color="yellow">I'll stick to him like a bodyguard
and take him around with me!</font>

279
00:20:52,099 --> 00:20:56,228
<font color="yellow">Chung-ja, how dare you! It doesn't matter
that he has the mind of a child right now!</font>

280
00:20:57,201 --> 00:20:58,557
<font color="yellow">What? Take him around with you?</font>

281
00:20:59,748 --> 00:21:00,748
<font color="yellow">I'm sorry.</font>

282
00:21:01,630 --> 00:21:03,130
<font color="yellow">I'll take care of him very well.</font>

283
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:06,877
<font color="yellow">You can leave him at home, grandfather.</font>

284
00:21:07,513 --> 00:21:10,604
<font color="yellow">Mother will protect him well.</font>

285
00:21:11,138 --> 00:21:12,138
<font color="yellow">No, it's fine.</font>

286
00:21:12,537 --> 00:21:16,151
<font color="yellow">After my meeting today,
we're going to go to the</font>

287
00:21:16,176 --> 00:21:20,380
<font color="yellow">dumpling store to pay them
back for the dumpling he ate.</font>

288
00:21:20,662 --> 00:21:21,662
<font color="yellow">Dumpling?</font>

289
00:21:22,576 --> 00:21:23,841
<font color="yellow">Yes, dumpling.</font>

290
00:21:24,545 --> 00:21:29,417
<font color="yellow">It tasted exactly like the ones
my mother used to make.</font>

291
00:21:30,146 --> 00:21:33,501
<font color="yellow">- Yes.
- Father and I will go
and buy a lot of dumplings.</font>

292
00:21:34,693 --> 00:21:35,794
<font color="yellow">Okay, dad.</font>

293
00:21:36,263 --> 00:21:38,614
<font color="yellow">- Dae-hoon, let's go.
- Yes, father.</font>

294
00:21:40,045 --> 00:21:41,433
<font color="yellow">Bye.</font>

295
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:43,583
<font color="yellow">I'll see you later.</font>

296
00:21:46,076 --> 00:21:52,297
<font color="yellow">But what if his memory comes back
while he's with Mr. Kim?</font>

297
00:21:52,927 --> 00:21:55,566
<font color="yellow">We need to separate those two somehow.</font>

298
00:21:56,505 --> 00:21:58,838
<font color="yellow">Grandfather became sensitive
because of what happened,</font>

299
00:21:58,863 --> 00:22:01,115
<font color="yellow">so let's take some time to think
about a way to solve this.</font>

300
00:22:01,334 --> 00:22:03,442
<font color="yellow">If we make the wrong move,
they might suspect us.</font>

301
00:22:06,154 --> 00:22:10,513
<font color="yellow">That's true. We did touch
the tiger's whiskers.</font>

302
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:15,747
<font color="yellow">- Hey, bring that in here.
- Welcome- oh! Hello, ma'am!</font>

303
00:22:15,772 --> 00:22:17,450
<font color="yellow">- Hi.
- Hello.</font>

304
00:22:17,787 --> 00:22:18,920
<font color="yellow">- Hello.
- Hello.</font>

305
00:22:19,623 --> 00:22:22,764
<font color="yellow">Congratulations! I wish you success!</font>

306
00:22:23,287 --> 00:22:26,400
<font color="yellow">If you need any extra help, call me anytime.</font>

307
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:29,646
<font color="yellow">Oh, thank you for your kind words.</font>

308
00:22:30,411 --> 00:22:32,661
<font color="yellow">- Put that up there.
- Yes, grandma.</font>

309
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:34,294
<font color="yellow">Oh, what's this?</font>

310
00:22:35,043 --> 00:22:39,222
<font color="yellow">It's kimchi. It was fermented
very well, so I brought it.</font>

311
00:22:39,247 --> 00:22:41,015
<font color="yellow">You can use it in your kimchi dumplings.</font>

312
00:22:41,271 --> 00:22:44,323
<font color="yellow">Oh, you didn't have
to do that. Thank you.</font>

313
00:22:44,348 --> 00:22:47,122
<font color="yellow">Please have a seat. I'll prepare
a plate of dumplings for you.</font>

314
00:22:47,147 --> 00:22:52,489
<font color="yellow">Oh, dear. We're not your customers.
Just treat us comfortably.</font>

315
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:55,681
<font color="yellow">Ms. Joo, please give me ten packs of dumplings</font>

316
00:22:55,706 --> 00:22:57,967
<font color="yellow">so I can give them to my theater colleagues.</font>

317
00:22:57,992 --> 00:23:00,302
<font color="yellow">- Sure. Please wait a moment.
- Okay.</font>

318
00:23:01,154 --> 00:23:02,521
<font color="yellow">Where's Mi-poong?</font>

319
00:23:03,083 --> 00:23:05,590
<font color="yellow">She took Yoo-sung to school.</font>

320
00:23:05,615 --> 00:23:06,615
<font color="yellow">I see.</font>

321
00:23:13,091 --> 00:23:14,091
<font color="yellow">Here you go.</font>

322
00:23:14,599 --> 00:23:19,779
<font color="yellow">- Here.
- No, you don't have to pay me.
You even brought kimchi for me.</font>

323
00:23:19,804 --> 00:23:23,139
<font color="yellow">- That's not even my kimchi. Please take it.
- Oh, no!</font>

324
00:23:23,163 --> 00:23:24,887
<font color="yellow">- Grandma, I'm going!
- Bye.</font>

325
00:23:24,912 --> 00:23:25,912
<font color="yellow">Bye!</font>

326
00:23:26,825 --> 00:23:30,650
<font color="yellow">- Ma'am...
- Just take it. It'll make
everyone feel comfortable.</font>

327
00:23:31,873 --> 00:23:34,268
<font color="yellow">All right. Thank you.</font>

328
00:23:57,521 --> 00:23:59,988
<font color="yellow">What's wrong? Do you know him?</font>

329
00:24:02,662 --> 00:24:03,943
<font color="yellow">The truth is...</font>

330
00:24:06,091 --> 00:24:07,669
<font color="yellow">I saw my husband yesterday.</font>

331
00:24:08,123 --> 00:24:11,044
<font color="yellow">What? Are you serious?</font>

332
00:24:11,951 --> 00:24:16,769
<font color="yellow">Your husband is really alive in Seoul?</font>

333
00:24:17,263 --> 00:24:18,989
<font color="yellow">I think so.</font>

334
00:24:21,037 --> 00:24:24,341
<font color="yellow">But he must be living on the streets.</font>

335
00:24:25,138 --> 00:24:28,524
<font color="yellow">Mi-poong said that
his appearance was terrible.</font>

336
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,755
<font color="yellow">I feel like he'll come back again.</font>

337
00:24:32,255 --> 00:24:35,715
<font color="yellow">That's why every time a man passes by,
I can't help but check on him.</font>

338
00:24:36,755 --> 00:24:38,658
<font color="yellow">Oh my goodness!</font>

339
00:24:39,248 --> 00:24:43,247
<font color="yellow">How could something like that happen?</font>

340
00:24:46,310 --> 00:24:47,643
<font color="yellow">You don't look well.</font>

341
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:50,177
<font color="yellow">Why? Is something wrong?</font>

342
00:24:51,420 --> 00:24:52,583
<font color="yellow">I don't know.</font>

343
00:24:53,653 --> 00:24:55,669
<font color="yellow">Nothing works out the way I want it to.</font>

344
00:24:56,623 --> 00:24:58,260
<font color="yellow">Are you holding a candle to the sun?</font>

345
00:24:59,146 --> 00:25:03,290
<font color="yellow">Who else has a better life than you?
You must be joking.</font>

346
00:25:04,232 --> 00:25:07,366
<font color="yellow">Fine. I'm sorry for complaining
when my life is perfect.</font>

347
00:25:08,341 --> 00:25:10,741
<font color="yellow">But what did you need to see me for?</font>

348
00:25:12,912 --> 00:25:16,429
<font color="yellow">I want you to find a prospective
marriage partner for Jang-go.</font>

349
00:25:16,740 --> 00:25:18,684
<font color="yellow">You said you would take responsibility and</font>

350
00:25:18,709 --> 00:25:20,693
<font color="yellow">find marriage partners for him
once he gets a divorce.</font>

351
00:25:20,865 --> 00:25:21,997
<font color="yellow">What's with you?</font>

352
00:25:22,888 --> 00:25:26,031
<font color="yellow">You said you would do this after
the consideration period is over.</font>

353
00:25:26,732 --> 00:25:32,982
<font color="yellow">Mi-poong signed the divorce papers but
continued to meet Jang-go behind my back.</font>

354
00:25:33,872 --> 00:25:36,342
<font color="yellow">And now, she even took his money.</font>

355
00:25:36,755 --> 00:25:37,755
<font color="yellow">What?</font>

356
00:25:38,231 --> 00:25:42,199
<font color="yellow">Oh my goodness.
She has no conscience whatsoever.</font>

357
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:46,620
<font color="yellow">Mi-poong and her mother took his money
and opened up a dumpling store.</font>

358
00:25:46,943 --> 00:25:48,599
<font color="yellow">What? A dumpling store?</font>

359
00:25:48,857 --> 00:25:49,857
<font color="yellow">Yes!</font>

360
00:25:50,755 --> 00:25:54,601
<font color="yellow">I was so stunned and
frustrated thinking about how she</font>

361
00:25:54,627 --> 00:25:58,751
<font color="yellow">ruined my son's life and took
his money that I almost died!</font>

362
00:25:58,904 --> 00:26:02,778
<font color="yellow">Goodness. Of course you'd feel that way.
Didn't you do anything about it though?</font>

363
00:26:03,162 --> 00:26:05,421
<font color="yellow">You should've grabbed
her hair and ripped it off!</font>

364
00:26:05,865 --> 00:26:09,368
<font color="yellow">I really wanted to do that, but I held it in.</font>

365
00:26:11,295 --> 00:26:14,708
<font color="yellow">It's like he gave her an alimony,
so they're totally over now.</font>

366
00:26:15,373 --> 00:26:20,332
<font color="yellow">So even if I tell him to date other women,
he'll have no other choice but to.</font>

367
00:26:21,123 --> 00:26:23,724
<font color="yellow">Okay, don't worry. Just trust me.</font>

368
00:26:28,209 --> 00:26:29,468
<font color="yellow">Are you coming just now?</font>

369
00:26:30,716 --> 00:26:33,200
<font color="yellow">Hello, ma'am.</font>

370
00:26:33,982 --> 00:26:37,174
<font color="yellow">Are you standing up to go
just because I'm here?</font>

371
00:26:37,685 --> 00:26:40,485
<font color="yellow">Don't worry about me and stay here longer.</font>

372
00:26:40,849 --> 00:26:43,442
<font color="yellow">Have some dumplings as well.</font>

373
00:26:43,467 --> 00:26:45,023
<font color="yellow">- Try them.
